From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: local <local@example.invalid>
Date: Thu, 25 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] vo: force nominal display fps for display-sync

Windows Vulkan/present paths can report a correct specified display FPS
(for example exact 24000/1001) while the measured refresh converges near
24/1.  If accepted, display-sync can pull NTSC-rate video to 24.000.

For this custom build, keep display-sync on the specified/nominal display
FPS by preventing the estimated interval from replacing the internal sync
interval.  This intentionally does not change stats-facing properties.
---
 video/out/vo.c | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/video/out/vo.c b/video/out/vo.c
--- a/video/out/vo.c
+++ b/video/out/vo.c
@@ -412,6 +412,20 @@ static void check_estimated_display_fps(struct vo *vo)
 {
     struct vo_internal *in = vo->in;
 
+    // Short-term Windows/Vulkan display-sync workaround.
+    //
+    // Some Windows Vulkan/present paths can report a correct specified display
+    // FPS (for example exact 24000/1001), while the measured/estimated refresh
+    // converges near the rounded integer mode (24/1).  If this estimated value
+    // is accepted, display-sync can pull exact NTSC-rate video to the rounded
+    // rate and cause long-term A/V drift.
+    //
+    // For this custom build, always keep display-sync on the specified/nominal
+    // display FPS.  Do not change stats-facing estimated-display-fps; this only
+    // prevents the estimate from becoming the internal sync interval.
+    in->vsync_interval = in->nominal_vsync_interval;
+    return;
+
     bool use_estimated = false;
     if (in->num_total_vsync_samples >= MAX_VSYNC_SAMPLES / 2 &&
         in->estimated_vsync_interval <= 1e9 / 20.0 &&
